18:56.322 --> 19:00.229
Okay, y'all, this is the God of all the universe.

19:01.631 --> 19:03.374
Do you think he didn't know where they were?

19:03.434 --> 19:10.126
Like, do you really think God does not know your worries?

19:11.869 --> 19:16.416
Do you think you're that much smarter than God that you can hide that from him?

19:17.458 --> 19:19.762
Do you really think God doesn't know your fears?

19:21.058 --> 19:26.464
Do you really think that God doesn't know what's robbing your joy or robbing your peace?

19:26.484 --> 19:29.507
Do you really think we can conveniently just hide that behind our back?

19:29.607 --> 19:30.929
Oh God, there's nothing here.

19:32.931 --> 19:37.396
God would rather us pray honest prayers than safe prayers.

19:39.338 --> 19:42.161
Safe prayers are, oh God, everything's perfect.

19:43.362 --> 19:45.144
Look at my Instagram, perfect life.

19:46.285 --> 19:47.106
Everything is great.

19:47.787 --> 19:50.450
Thank you God, amen.

19:51.554 --> 19:52.435
That's safe prayers.

19:53.496 --> 19:56.098
Honest prayers are sometimes like, God, this is terrible.

19:57.820 --> 19:59.201
God, I don't know what you're doing.

20:01.003 --> 20:02.605
This doesn't make a lick of sense.

20:03.706 --> 20:06.128
I'm scared and I'm angry.

20:07.649 --> 20:12.174
I don't know if any of y'all have ever seen the old movie, The Apostle with Robert Duvall.

20:14.916 --> 20:15.597
Why am I not surprised?

20:15.817 --> 20:16.498
You've seen it, Mike.

20:16.518 --> 20:16.978
Why does that?

20:18.099 --> 20:18.980
Isn't it a great movie?

20:19.461 --> 20:20.882
Like in this movie,

20:21.474 --> 20:28.421
Billy Bob Thornton gets saved, and it may be, it's one of the best things I cry when I watch it.

20:29.262 --> 20:32.426
It's the most authentic conversion I've ever seen in my entire life.

20:32.446 --> 20:39.193
So I'm not gonna, okay, it starts off, he kills his youth pastor, but let's be honest, who amongst us hadn't wanted to do that at some point?

20:40.675 --> 20:43.898
Oh, sorry, maybe I didn't see there.

20:47.382 --> 20:51.186
So, and then he's on the run from the cop for a lot of the rest of the movie.

20:51.394 --> 20:53.437
It doesn't paint him as a perfect character.

20:54.978 --> 21:05.111
But there's this one scene where he is, he went to his mom's house who is paid, played by Ruth Carter Cash and she's asleep and he's in the basement just yelling at God, just yelling.

21:07.334 --> 21:10.678
And somebody calls his mom and says, Hey, what's going on?

21:10.698 --> 21:12.000
Is there a mad man in your house?

21:13.422 --> 21:14.483
She said, No, that's just sunny.

21:15.724 --> 21:16.866
Sometimes he talks to God.

21:16.886 --> 21:17.767
Sometimes he yells.

21:19.409 --> 21:20.210
Tonight he's yelling.

21:23.906 --> 21:24.947
That's an honest prayer.

21:27.730 --> 21:28.971
Because you know what God is?

21:30.913 --> 21:31.854
Big enough to handle it.

21:34.596 --> 21:41.623
If we serve a God who is too small to handle our human frailties, how small of a God is that?

21:41.643 --> 21:44.065
That's not the God of Scripture, friends.

21:45.066 --> 21:46.267
That's not the God of Scripture.

21:46.527 --> 21:49.710
The God of Scripture can handle all that we deal with.

21:50.791 --> 21:53.554
All of our fears, all of our... That's what Paul says.

21:53.794 --> 21:55.116
with prayer and supplication.

21:56.517 --> 22:04.548
Don't worry about anything, but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving, let your request be made known to God.

22:04.568 --> 22:05.449
So take it to God.

22:05.509 --> 22:06.911
Take it to God.

22:07.692 --> 22:11.557
Take your fears, take your doubts, take your worries, take your concerns.

22:12.498 --> 22:14.380
Well, but there's bigger things out there.

22:14.621 --> 22:20.748
Well, everybody's got something, of course, but if it matters to you, it matters to God.

22:21.229 --> 22:21.970
The Bible says,

22:22.498 --> 22:25.202
that God knows the hairs on your hair on your head.

22:25.523 --> 22:30.471
The Bible says, does not a sparrow fall from the sky that your father's not aware of?

22:30.671 --> 22:32.715
We're like, oh, sweet little sparrows.

22:32.835 --> 22:34.277
Y'all, sparrows were nasty.

22:35.560 --> 22:37.122
They were rats with good PR.

22:39.226 --> 22:49.202
Nobody likes sparrows if you committed a sin and you were too poor and too indigent and too broken down to afford a proper sacrifice

22:49.922 --> 22:51.745
You sacrifice sparrows.

22:52.065 --> 22:57.754
Sparrows are at the bottom of the food chain, literally, spiritually, and figuratively.

23:00.137 --> 23:05.345
There's not a sparrow fall from the sky that your father's not aware of.

23:08.770 --> 23:09.831
God loves you, friends.

23:11.954 --> 23:16.741
Your concerns, your fears, your brokenness, they matter to God.

23:18.164 --> 23:19.826
So we take these things to God

23:22.146 --> 23:31.438
And then when we take these things to God, the peace that passes all understanding will guard our hearts and minds with Christ Jesus.

23:33.520 --> 23:48.659
Well, the reason why these things guard our hearts and minds in Christ Jesus is because when we take them to God, we realize we serve a God who's big enough to handle them.

23:48.679 --> 23:51.122
We serve a God who's big enough to handle our fears.

23:53.154 --> 23:56.338
We serve a God who's big enough to handle what we released to Him.

23:58.161 --> 24:02.507
When we let it go, we find we have a God who can handle it.

24:05.030 --> 24:06.592
This world's hard, it did, y'all.

24:11.038 --> 24:11.559
You don't believe me?

24:11.579 --> 24:12.500
Just log on to Facebook.

24:12.520 --> 24:14.042
Everybody's mad about something all the time.

24:16.926 --> 24:17.547
And it's scary.

24:19.609 --> 24:20.431
It's alienating.

24:22.233 --> 24:22.994
It's divisive.

24:24.130 --> 24:36.549
By the way, when you keep reading John 17, that chapter I talked about, the pastoral prayer, do you know what Jesus prays for twice in there, both for the apostles in that moment and for the church that is to come?

24:37.250 --> 24:39.713
He says, I pray that they may be one as we are one.

24:41.756 --> 24:43.479
Why is unity the first thing we throw out?

24:47.124 --> 24:48.527
Why is unity the first thing we throw out?

24:48.587 --> 24:49.848
Jesus prayed for our unity.

24:51.531 --> 24:53.554
One of my desires for St. Matthew's

24:54.402 --> 25:05.523
It's for us to be a place where regardless of what you believe theologically, what you believe politically, what you believe in all these things, you can find a place to belong here.

25:06.445 --> 25:10.332
There are not many places left in our world where that's the place.

25:11.735 --> 25:13.759
That sounds great on bumper sticker.

25:13.939 --> 25:14.681
Here's the problem.

25:14.701 --> 25:15.142
You know the problem?

25:15.162 --> 25:17.426
That is people are going to always be people.

25:18.914 --> 25:21.477
If you're in relation with people who disagree with you, they're going to get on your nerve.

25:21.497 --> 25:22.217
They're going to annoy you.

25:22.237 --> 25:23.038
They're going to offend you.

25:23.058 --> 25:24.139
They're going to make you angry.

25:24.319 --> 25:29.304
And it's going to be very tempting and very easy to cut off relationship.

25:31.506 --> 25:47.602
My friend Keith Keaton, who's a pastor in Hattiesburg, likes to say that being in relationship with those with whom you disagree is a means of grace because it makes us humble ourselves.

25:48.802 --> 25:50.284
It makes us pray.

25:51.286 --> 25:55.152
It makes us lean into each other and not away from each other.

25:55.553 --> 25:56.394
And that's hard.

25:57.336 --> 25:58.298
That is so hard.

25:59.419 --> 26:01.683
So it depends upon Jesus for us to do that.

26:05.149 --> 26:10.738
But when we give our concerns to Jesus, we find that we serve a God bigger than all of this.

26:11.970 --> 26:23.597
I got bigger than I, and when we realized the vastness and the hugeness and the might and the strength and the power of God, what are these momentary things in this life, friends?

26:24.799 --> 26:28.708
That thing right now that's dropping your peace, you're not even gonna think about it in a year from now, are you?

26:29.290 --> 26:30.212
About five years from now.

26:30.232 --> 26:31.154
About 10 years from now.

26:31.362 --> 26:33.545
Where's it going to rank in the light of eternity?

26:33.766 --> 26:38.093
These things that rob our peace, that rob our joy, that rob our strength, that rob our lives.

26:38.113 --> 26:41.919
These things, where do they rank in the light of eternity?

26:41.939 --> 26:42.600
They do not.

26:44.062 --> 26:45.364
Turn your eyes upon Jesus.

26:45.404 --> 26:51.874
Look full in his wonderful face and the things of this earth will grow strangely dim in the light of his glory and grace.

26:53.357 --> 26:56.722
Cast your cares upon him because he cares for you.

26:57.442 --> 27:02.608
And then that peace will guard your hearts and souls and minds in Christ Jesus.

27:04.870 --> 27:06.231
Oh, at peace we often forfeit.

27:07.213 --> 27:12.438
Oh, what needless pain we bear, all because we do not carry everything to God in prayer.

27:14.641 --> 27:15.421
That's a prayer, yes.

27:18.625 --> 27:19.386
Not about the words.

27:21.808 --> 27:22.529
It's about the awareness.

27:25.452 --> 27:27.154
One of my favorite verses that has changed

27:27.650 --> 27:29.252
how much, so much of how I'll understand God.

27:30.213 --> 27:38.705
It's Jesus's teaching and he says, if you who are sinful know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more does your perfect heavenly Father know how to give you good gifts?

27:39.666 --> 27:46.496
I think about that a lot like if I'm gonna want the best for my children and I'm an imperfect person, how much more is God gonna want the best for me, right?

27:47.137 --> 27:52.965
So one of the things I've heard, sometimes people talk about praying and this helps us to understand that it's about presence.

27:54.286 --> 27:57.010
You ever been praying at night and fall asleep

27:57.858 --> 28:02.124
And feel frustrated, like, come on, man, like Peter, can you not tear you one hour longer?

28:06.230 --> 28:12.318
As a parent, what is more beautiful than having your child fall asleep in your arms?

28:15.883 --> 28:21.251
And we're praying we drift off the sleep.

28:21.271 --> 28:26.578
We're simply a trusting child falling asleep in the arms of our loving father.

28:29.858 --> 28:38.791
Cast your cares upon God in this peace that passes all understanding will guard your heart's souls and minds in Christ Jesus.

28:41.235 --> 28:41.715
He loves you.

28:43.398 --> 28:45.781
He truly and deeply loves you.

28:47.624 --> 28:49.827
And we cast all that we are upon Him.

28:51.109 --> 28:54.214
We find the depth of His love for us.

28:56.517 --> 28:59.762
Today, friends, know how deeply you are loved.

29:01.442 --> 29:03.902
And the name of the Father and the Son, the Holy Spirit.

29:04.427 --> 29:04.850
Let's pray.

